**Title:** Contact damage: standard enemies (hearts, i-frames, knockback)

## Body
## Parent

#1

## What to build

When the player’s hurtbox overlaps a **standard enemy** (the `enemies` collection), the player takes **1 heart** of damage, plays the existing **hit reaction**, and is pushed out of overlap via **knockback**. Damage is gated by the existing invulnerability window (`hitCooldownDuration`), so sustained overlap can’t drain multiple hearts instantly.

## Acceptance criteria

- [ ] Overlapping `player.hitbox` with a standard enemy’s `hitbox` removes **exactly 1 heart** and reduces player HP by 1.
- [ ] While the player is invulnerable (cooldown active), additional overlaps do **not** remove more hearts.
- [ ] On hit, player plays the hit reaction and receives knockback **away from** the enemy (horizontal push, with a small upward bump if needed).
- [ ] Contact damage is based on collision boxes/hitboxes (not visuals) and does not trigger when the run is already ended (e.g. player is in Game Over / dead).

